[
    {
        "source_sentence": "大般涅槃經集解卷第六十二",
        "translation": "Mahāparinirvāṇa-sūtra, Collected and Explained, Volume 62",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b16_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "　舉盲人說象譬",
        "translation": "to cite the parable of the blind man speaking of the elephant",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b18_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "　明佛性不即六法不離六法義",
        "translation": "clarifying the meaning that the buddha-nature is not the same as the six dharmas and not separate from the six dharmas",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b19_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "　明佛性十二因緣信等",
        "translation": "clarification of the buddha-nature of twelve causes and conditions of faith and so forth",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b20_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "　辨菩薩不退相日食一麻一豆等事",
        "translation": "Explaining the nonretrogression of the bodhisattvas, such as eating one hempseed and one soybean per day",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b21_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "　出菩薩以身施眾生發願事",
        "translation": "the vow that arises when a bodhisattva gives his body to sentient beings",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b22_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "　出菩薩為眾生受苦不退事",
        "translation": "the bodhisattvas who emerge from the world of suffering and non-retrogression for the sake of sentient beings",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b23_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "　出天海八種不思議譬",
        "translation": "eight unfathomable parables of the Vaiśravaṇa Sea",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b24_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "師子吼品之第九",
        "translation": "the ninth rank of the lion's roar",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b25_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "善男子譬如有王告一大臣(至)以是故說色為佛性。",
        "translation": "\"Good sons, it's like a king who told a minister (to) therefore explain that form is the buddha-nature.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b26_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "Commentary.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b27_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b27_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "各以手觸者。",
        "translation": "\"Each person touches it with their hand.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b27_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "譬聞見也。",
        "translation": "It's a metaphor for hearing and seeing.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b27_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "同不說象體。",
        "translation": "They're both not talking about the elephant's body.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b27_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "偏見非象。",
        "translation": "They're prejudiced in seeing what's not an elephant.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b28_6",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "亦非不說者。",
        "translation": "Nor is it someone who doesn't explain it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b28_7",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "各得其分。",
        "translation": "Each has his part.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b28_8",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "非不說也。",
        "translation": "It's not something that isn't explained.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b29_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "色是佛性者。",
        "translation": "'Form is the buddha-nature'?",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b29_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "正因性異。",
        "translation": "It's precisely because their natures are different.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b29_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "成果亦異。",
        "translation": "The results are also different.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570b29_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "以偏著為失也。",
        "translation": "It's a mistake to be partially attached to it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c01_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "如金色是一槃蛇為異也。",
        "translation": "Just as gold is a serpent in one panacea, so it's different.'",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c01_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧宗曰。",
        "translation": "The Saṃgha School says.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c01_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第二翻也。",
        "translation": "\"The second explanation is this.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c02_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "明如來說性不同。",
        "translation": "It explains that the Tathāgata's explanation of nature is different.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c02_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "凡夫既真而無謬。",
        "translation": "Since it's true and not mistaken, ordinary people should cultivate it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c02_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "故應修也。",
        "translation": "Therefore, they should cultivate it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c03_6",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "王者譬佛。",
        "translation": "The king is a metaphor for the Buddha.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c03_7",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "臣者譬常住經教。",
        "translation": "The minister is a metaphor for the teaching of an eternally abiding scripture.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c03_8",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "象譬教下理也。",
        "translation": "The elephant metaphorically represents the principle beneath the teaching.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c04_9",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "盲者隨所觸而說象。",
        "translation": "A blind man follows what he touches and then speaks of an elephant.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c04_10",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "眾生無慧。",
        "translation": "Sentient beings lack wisdom.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c04_11",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "乃計陰說我也。",
        "translation": "They then impute aggregates and speak of a self.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c05_12",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "說離陰有我者。",
        "translation": "Someone who says there's a self apart from the aggregates ...",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c05_13",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "此計太過。",
        "translation": "This calculation is too much.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c05_14",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "下當非之也。",
        "translation": "The following should reject it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c06_15",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "非即六法。",
        "translation": "What's not is the six dharmas.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c06_16",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "不離六法者。",
        "translation": "Those who aren't free from the six dharmas.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c06_17",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "以五陰成假名人。",
        "translation": "It's because the five aggregates form a nominal name for a person.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c06_18",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "佛性在果。",
        "translation": "The buddha-nature is in the result.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c07_19",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "豈即六法非因。",
        "translation": "Does that mean the six dharmas aren't causes?",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c07_20",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "無以感果。",
        "translation": "There's no way to bring about the result.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c07_21",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "故言不離也。",
        "translation": "That's why it's called not separate from them.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c08_22",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "寶亮曰。",
        "translation": "Baoliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c08_23",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "盲人觸象。",
        "translation": "\"A blind man touches an elephant.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c08_24",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "若一一而望。",
        "translation": "If they look at each one, they won't see the elephant's body.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c08_25",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "不得象體。",
        "translation": "They can't perceive the elephant's body.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c09_26",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "然復不得離此而有象也。",
        "translation": "Still, it can't be separated from that and have an elephant.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c09_27",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "外道凡夫。",
        "translation": "Non-Buddhist worldlings.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c09_28",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "捉五陰及離陰。",
        "translation": "They grasp the five aggregates and free aggregates.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c10_29",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "一一計非佛性。",
        "translation": "Each one of them is not considered to be buddha-nature.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c10_30",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "然始終不離此六法也。",
        "translation": "Yet, they never part from these six dharmas in the beginning or end.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c10_31",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "有諸外道。",
        "translation": "There are non-Buddhists.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c11_32",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "雖說有我。",
        "translation": "Even though they say there's a self, there's really no self.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c11_33",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "而實無我者。",
        "translation": "They really don't have a self.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c11_34",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "破第六別計五陰外有我。",
        "translation": "They refute the sixth specific notion that there's a self outside of the five aggregates.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c12_35",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "謂五陰假合。",
        "translation": "It means the five aggregates are falsely combined.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c12_36",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "名為眾生。",
        "translation": "They're called sentient beings.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c13_37",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "無別五陰外有我也。",
        "translation": "There's no separate existence of a self outside of the five aggregates.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c13_38",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "或有說言受是佛性(至)乃至非我不離我。",
        "translation": "Some people say that feeling is the buddha-nature ... and that it's not self and not separate from self.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c14_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "Commentary.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c14_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c15_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "上舉色。",
        "translation": "\"The above cited form.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c15_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "今舉心歷心。",
        "translation": "Now, it's citing the mind and going through the thoughts.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c15_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "稱四陰也。",
        "translation": "It's called the four aggregates.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c15_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "善男子有諸外道雖說有我(至)第一義空故名佛性。",
        "translation": "\"Good sons, although some non-Buddhists say there's a self, it's called buddha-nature because of the emptiness of the ultimate truth.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c16_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "Commentary.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c17_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c17_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "就惑情為離也。",
        "translation": "'Regarding the afflictive feelings as free,' he said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c17_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "故是即陰我相續不斷耳。",
        "translation": "Therefore, it means that the aggregates and self are continuous and uninterrupted.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c17_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "後還正之。",
        "translation": "He later returned to it correctly.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c18_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "謂離陰別我也。",
        "translation": "It's being free of the aggregates and the distinct self.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c18_6",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "善男子大慈大悲名為佛性(至)佛性者即是如來。",
        "translation": "\"Good sons, great kindness and great compassion are called the buddha-nature (to the extent that) the buddha-nature is the Tathāgata.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c19_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "Commentary.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c20_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c20_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "說緣因性。",
        "translation": "\"It's called the causal nature of conditions.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c20_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "眾生必得。",
        "translation": "It's bound to be attained by sentient beings.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c20_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "故名有也。",
        "translation": "Therefore, it's called 'existence.'",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c20_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "相續不異。",
        "translation": "Their continuity isn't different.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c21_6",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "即如來也。",
        "translation": "This is the Tathāgata.'",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c21_7",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧宗曰。",
        "translation": "The Saṃgha School said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c21_8",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第三出佛性體也。",
        "translation": "\"The third thing that comes out is the essence of the buddha-nature.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c21_9",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "寶亮曰。",
        "translation": "Baoliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c22_10",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第四歷緣因四無量行。",
        "translation": "\"The fourth relates to the causes of the four immeasurable practices.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c22_11",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "即是緣因。",
        "translation": "These are the causes of conditions.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c22_12",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "善菩薩常行。",
        "translation": "The good bodhisattva always conducts himself.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c23_13",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "如影隨形也。",
        "translation": "They are like shadows following forms.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c23_14",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "佛性名如來者。",
        "translation": "The Buddha-nature is called the Tathāgata.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c23_15",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "行四無量。",
        "translation": "He performs four immeasurable practices.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c24_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "近得初住一字之地。",
        "translation": "Nearby, he attains the first abode of the one-word stage.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c24_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "遠則圓滿得佛。",
        "translation": "From afar, he'll fully attain Buddhahood.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c24_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "故名如來也。",
        "translation": "That's why it's called the tathāgata.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c25_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "佛性者名大信心(至)一切眾生悉有佛性。",
        "translation": "\"Buddha-nature\" is called great faith (to the extent that) all sentient beings have buddha-nature.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c26_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "Commentary.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c26_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c27_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "舉六法門。",
        "translation": "\"He cites six dharma approaches.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c27_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "助顯其旨也。",
        "translation": "They help to clarify their meaning.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c27_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "善男子如上所說種種諸法(至)一切眾生悉有佛性。",
        "translation": "\"Good sons, as the various dharmas described above (have arrived), all sentient beings possess the buddha-nature.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c28_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "Commentary.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c29_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Saṃgha Liang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c29_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "總結上旨也。",
        "translation": "\"This sums up the above teaching.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0570c29_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "善男子若說色是佛性者(至)乃至說識亦復如是。",
        "translation": "\"Good sons, if you say that form is the buddha-nature (up to) and you say that consciousness is likewise,\" he said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a01_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "Commentary.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a02_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Saṃgha Liang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a02_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "若說色是佛性。",
        "translation": "\"If it's said that form is the buddha-nature, then the rest isn't.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a02_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "餘非者。",
        "translation": "The rest is not.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a02_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "耶見眾生。",
        "translation": "Yes, they see sentient beings.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a02_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "聞必起倒也。",
        "translation": "They'll surely become mistaken when they hear it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a03_6",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "善男子若諸眾生了佛性者(至)兼復讚歎禮拜問說。",
        "translation": "\"Good sons, if sentient beings have understood the buddha-nature, they'll praise, worship, and ask about it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a04_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "Commentary.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a05_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a05_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "既勸修此經名。",
        "translation": "\"Since they're encouraged to cultivate the name of this sūtra.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a05_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "故說修者之福也。",
        "translation": "Therefore, it explains the merits of those who cultivate it.'",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a05_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧宗曰。",
        "translation": "Saṃgha Zong said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a06_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第四正勸修也。",
        "translation": "\"The fourth proper exhortation is to cultivate it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a06_6",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "寶亮曰。",
        "translation": "Baoliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a06_7",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第五結勸。",
        "translation": "\"The fifth concluding exhortation is this.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a06_8",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "明應須修道之意也。",
        "translation": "It clarifies the intention that cultivation should be undertaken.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a07_9",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "善男子若有已於過去無量(至)然後乃得聞是經名。",
        "translation": "\"Good sons, if there were people in the past without measure (to) then they would have heard the name of this sūtra.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a08_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "Commentary.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a09_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Senlvān said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a09_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "歎修者之因也。",
        "translation": "\"This is the cause for praising those who cultivate.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a09_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "善男子佛性不可思議(至)大涅槃經亦不可思議。",
        "translation": "\"Good sons, the nature of the Buddha is inconceivable.\" (Until) The Mahāparinirvāṇa-sūtra is also inconceivable.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a10_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "Commentary.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a11_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a11_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "歎三寶佛性經法不可議。",
        "translation": "\"The sutra praising the Three Treasures' Buddha-nature is inconceivable.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a11_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "顯勸修之旨不虛也。",
        "translation": "It shows that the purpose of encouraging cultivation isn't false.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a12_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "師子吼菩薩言世尊(至)得阿耨多羅三藐三菩提。",
        "translation": "Shizihao Pusa said, \"The Bhagavān (arrived) has attained supreme perfect enlightenment.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a13_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "Commentary.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a14_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a14_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "師子吼領。",
        "translation": "\"Shizi-hao led the way.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a14_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "并敘時眾得利益。",
        "translation": "He also described the benefits received by the multitude at that time.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a14_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "佛即印述也。",
        "translation": "The Buddha was also the one who sealed the explanation.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a15_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "師子吼言世尊云何不退(至)阿耨多羅三藐三菩提。",
        "translation": "Shizi Zhao said, \"Bhagavān, why doesn't he retrogress (to) unsurpassed, perfect enlightenment?",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a16_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "Commentary.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a17_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧宗曰。",
        "translation": "The Saṃgha School said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a17_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "此下修道之第七也。",
        "translation": "\"This is the seventh step of the path of cultivation.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a17_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "向以有性故。",
        "translation": "It's because there's a nature in the past.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a17_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "所以勸修。",
        "translation": "That's why it's encouraged to cultivate.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a18_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "言修行者。",
        "translation": "Those who say they're cultivating their practice ...",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a18_6",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "功業轉深。",
        "translation": "His merits become deeper.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a18_7",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "不復退轉。",
        "translation": "They won't turn back again.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a18_8",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "若不能深識經旨。",
        "translation": "If someone can't deeply understand the teaching of the sūtras.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a19_9",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "者則有退轉也。",
        "translation": "then there's regression.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a19_10",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "如此苦行。",
        "translation": "Such austerities are practiced.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a19_11",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "多是住前。",
        "translation": "It's mostly abiding in the past.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a20_12",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "言因經修行。",
        "translation": "It's called cultivating the practice of the sūtras.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a20_13",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "無利益事。",
        "translation": "It's not beneficial.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a20_14",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "尚為之。",
        "translation": "They still do it.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a20_15",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "豈況有益。",
        "translation": "How could it be helpful?",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a21_16",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "而當不為此。",
        "translation": "They mustn't do this.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a21_17",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "明人於經修行。",
        "translation": "It's clear that people cultivate the practice of the sūtras.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a21_18",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "得其理味。",
        "translation": "He acquires the taste of the principle.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a22_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "永不復退也。",
        "translation": "He'll never fall back.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a22_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "寶亮曰。",
        "translation": "Baoliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a22_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "此下修道之第七。",
        "translation": "\"This is the seventh of the following paths of cultivation.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a22_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "正出修道人相。",
        "translation": "It correctly presents the marks of a person who cultivates cultivation.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a23_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "上來雖勸其修道。",
        "translation": "Although the above person encouraged them to cultivate their religious practice.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a23_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "諸人咸然。",
        "translation": "All of them are like that.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a23_6",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "不知修道之法。",
        "translation": "They didn't know the way to cultivate cultivation.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a24_7",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "佛今略示其相。",
        "translation": "Now, the Buddha will briefly show them their characteristics.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a24_8",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "若能作如此苦行者是也。",
        "translation": "\"This is the person who does such ascetic practices.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a24_9",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "善男子菩薩摩訶薩(至)是名不退菩提之相。",
        "translation": "\"Good sons, bodhisattva-mahāsattva(-to) this is called the characteristic of nonretrogression to enlightenment.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a26_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "Commentary.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a27_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a27_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第七不退相門也。",
        "translation": "\"The seventh aspect of nonretrogression is also the aspect of nonretrogression.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a27_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "修道必生死。",
        "translation": "Cultivating the path necessarily entails birth-and-death.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a27_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "但生死多難。",
        "translation": "But birth-and-death is often difficult.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a27_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "不能自知退與不退。",
        "translation": "They can't know for themselves whether they're regressing or not regressing.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a28_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "次辨不退相也。",
        "translation": "This is followed by an explanation of the aspect of nonretrogression.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571a28_6",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "復次善男子菩薩摩訶薩(至)是故復名不可思議。",
        "translation": "\"Furthermore, good sons, the bodhisattvas, the great sons (to whom) it's further called inconceivable.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571b01_0",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "案。",
        "translation": "Commentary.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571b02_1",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "僧亮曰。",
        "translation": "Sengliang said.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571b02_2",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "第八歎不退菩薩。",
        "translation": "\"The eighth praises the nonretrogressing bodhisattva.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571b02_3",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "不思議德也。",
        "translation": "It's inconceivable in terms of virtue.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571b02_4",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "受後邊身者。",
        "translation": "He who receives the final body.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571b03_5",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "上說具煩惱性地解地。",
        "translation": "The above explains the ground of liberation with the nature of affliction.",
        "source": "T37n1763_062:0571b03_6",
        "is_bad_quality": false
    },
    {
        "source_sentence": "今說後身義其始終。",
